</table>
<h4><span class="editsection">[<a href="../../w/index-title=Confederate_States_of_America&action=edit&section=29.php.html" title="Edit section: Judicial">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline" id="Judicial">Judicial</span></h4>
<p>The Confederate Constitution outlined a judicial branch of the government, but the ongoing war and resistance from states-rights advocates, particularly on the question of whether it would have appellate jurisdiction over the state courts, prevented the creation or seating of the "Supreme Court of the Confederate States;" the state courts generally continued to operate as they had done, simply recognizing the Confederate States as the national government.<sup id="cite_ref-173" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-173"><span>[</span>173<span>]</span></a></sup></p>
<table style="float:right;">
<tr>
<td>
<ul class="gallery" style="max-width: 326px;_width: 326px;">
<li class="gallerybox" style="width: 155px">
<div style="width: 155px">
<div class="thumb" style="width: 150px;">
<div style="margin:15px auto;"><a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Jesse_Finley_-_Brady-Handy.jpg" class="image"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d8/Jesse_Finley_-_Brady-Handy.jpg/81px-Jesse_Finley_-_Brady-Handy.jpg" width="81" height="120" /></a></div>
</div>
<div class="gallerytext">
<center><a href="../Jesse_J._Finley" title="Jesse J. Finley">Jesse J. Finley</a><br />
